    <ActyNotPreviouslyRptExpln documentId="RetDoc2205400001">
      <ExplanationTxt>THE FOUNDATION OPERATES A PROGRAM IN WHICH IT PROVIDES FREE OR REDUCED RATE LEGAL SERVICES TO IMMIGRANTS UNDER THE AGE OF 21 WHO ARE PURSUING U.S. IMMIGRANT STATUS PRIMARILY UNDER THE SPECIAL IMMIGRANT JUVENILE STATUS ("SIJS") PROGRAM OF THE U.S. CITIZENSHIP AND IMMIGRATION SERVICES AGENCY. THE SIJS PROGRAM PROVIDES A PATH TO IMMIGRANT STATUS FOR MINORS WHO WERE VICTIMS OF ABUSE, NEGLECT OR ABANDONMENT IN THEIR HOME COUNTRIES. THE APPLICATION PROCESS IS COMPLEX, AND DIFFICULT TO NAVIGATE WITHOUT LEGAL COUNSEL. A NOMINAL FEE IS REQUESTED FOR THOSE WITH THE ABILITY TO PAY FOR THESE SERVICES, BUT FEES ARE WAIVED WHERE PAYMENT WOULD BE A HARDSHIP.</ExplanationTxt>
    </ActyNotPreviouslyRptExpln>
